    "from hestonpy.models.heston import Heston\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import numpy as np"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Hedging with Heston"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We delta and vega hedge with an other call with 110% of strike and 120% of time to maturity"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Computing option prices ...\n",
      "Computing vegas ...\n",
      "Computing deltas ...\n"
     ]
    },
    {
     "name": "stderr",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "100%|██████████| 251/251 [00:00<00:00, 9276.82it/s]\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Parameters for the Heston model\n",
    "S0 = 100.0  # Initial spot price\n",
    "V0 = 0.06  # Initial volatility\n",
    "r = 0.03  # Risk-free interest rate\n",
    "\n",
    "params = {\n",
    "    'kappa': 1.0,  # Mean reversion rate\n",
    "    'theta': 0.06,  # Long-term volatility\n",
    "    'drift_emm': 0.00,  # Drift term\n",
    "    'sigma': 0.3,  # Volatility of volatility\n",
    "    'rho': -0.5,  # Correlation between asset and volatility\n",
    "}\n",
    "heston = Heston(spot=S0, vol_initial=V0, r=r, **params)\n",
    "\n",
    "strike = 100\n",
    "strike_hedging = 110\n",
    "maturity = 1\n",
    "maturity_hedging = 1.2\n",
    "nbr_points = 252\n",
    "nbr_simulations = 1000\n",
    "\n",
    "portfolio, S, V, C = heston.delta_vega_hedging(\n",
    "    strike,\n",
    "    strike_hedging,\n",
    "    maturity,\n",
    "    maturity_hedging,\n",
    "    nbr_points, \n",
    "    nbr_simulations\n",
    ")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Replication errors"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Sanity check of the replication"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 9,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 500x500 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "ST = S[:, -1]\n",
    "VT = portfolio[:, -1]\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(5, 5))\n",
    "plt.title(\"Réplication du payoff\")\n",
    "plt.grid(linestyle=\"--\", dashes=(5, 10), color=\"gray\", linewidth=0.5)\n",
    "plt.minorticks_on()\n",
    "plt.xlabel(r\"$S_T$\")\n",
    "plt.ylabel(\"payoff\")\n",
    "plt.scatter(ST, VT, s=0.8, color=\"red\")\n",
    "x = np.linspace(min(ST), max(ST))\n",
    "payoff = np.maximum(0, x - strike)\n",
    "plt.plot(x, payoff, color=\"blue\")\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Sanity check of the replication"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 10,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1500x800 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "ST = S[:, -1]\n",
    "VT = portfolio[:, -1]\n",
    "\n",
    "from scipy.stats import norm\n",
    "\n",
    "cash_flows = np.maximum(0, ST - strike)\n",
    "hedging_errors = VT - cash_flows\n",
    "hedging_errors = hedging_errors[np.abs(hedging_errors) < 5]\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(15, 8))\n",
    "plt.hist(hedging_errors, bins=\"fd\", density=True, color=\"gray\", alpha=0.8)\n",
    "plt.axvline(np.mean(hedging_errors), color=\"black\", label=\"mean\", alpha=0.8)\n",
    "\n",
    "x = np.linspace(start=min(hedging_errors), stop=max(hedging_errors), num=100)\n",
    "plt.plot(\n",
    "    x,\n",
    "    norm.pdf(x, loc=np.mean(hedging_errors), scale=np.std(hedging_errors)),\n",
    "    label=\"normal density\",\n",
    "    color=\"blue\",\n",
    ")\n",
    "plt.xlabel(r\"Hedging errors: $V_T - (S_T - K)^+$\")\n",
    "plt.grid(linestyle=\"--\", dashes=(5, 10), color=\"gray\", linewidth=0.5)\n",
    "plt.minorticks_on()\n",
    "plt.legend()\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Evolution of the replication portfolio"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 11,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1500x800 with 2 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "time = np.linspace(start=0, stop=maturity, num=nbr_points + 1)\n",
    "\n",
    "path = -10\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, (ax1, ax2) = plt.subplots(2, figsize=(15, 8))\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.suptitle(\"Portefeuille de réplication\")\n",
    "\n",
    "ax1.plot(time, C[path, :], label=\"target call\")\n",
    "ax1.plot(time, portfolio[path, :], label=\"portfolio\")\n",
    "ax1.grid(linestyle=\"--\", dashes=(5, 10), color=\"gray\", linewidth=0.5)\n",
    "ax1.minorticks_on()\n",
    "ax1.legend()\n",
    "\n",
    "ax2.axhline(y=strike, label=\"Target strike\", linestyle=\"dashed\", color='black', linewidth=0.7)\n",
    "ax2.axhline(y=strike_hedging, label=\"Hedging strike\", linestyle=\"dashed\", color='black', linewidth=0.7)\n",
    "ax2.plot(time, S[path, :], label=\"Underlying\")\n",
    "ax2.grid(linestyle=\"--\", dashes=(5, 10), color=\"gray\", linewidth=0.5)\n",
    "ax2.minorticks_on()\n",
    "ax2.set_xlabel(\"Time\")\n",
    "ax2.legend()\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },

     "data": {
      "image/png": "",

       "<Figure size 1500x1000 with 3 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1500x1000 with 3 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "nbr_simulations_to_plot = 5\n",
    "time = np.linspace(start=0, stop=maturity, num=nbr_points + 1)\n",
    "paths = range(nbr_simulations_to_plot)\n",
    "\n",
    "for path in paths:\n",
    "\n",
    "    fig, (ax1, ax2, ax3) = plt.subplots(3, figsize=(15, 10))\n",
    "\n",
    "    plt.suptitle(f\"Portefeuille de réplication - simulation {path}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Tracé avec des styles différents\n",
    "    ax1.plot(time, portfolio[path, :], label=\"Portfolio\", color='blue', marker='+')\n",
    "    ax1.plot(time, C[path, :], label=\"Call\", color='red', marker='+')\n",
    "    ax1.grid(linestyle=\"--\", dashes=(5, 10), color=\"gray\", linewidth=0.5)\n",
    "    ax1.minorticks_on()\n",
    "    ax1.legend()\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Tracé avec des styles différents\n",
    "    ax2.plot(time, S[path, :], label=\"Risky asset\", color='red', marker='+')\n",
    "    ax2.grid(linestyle=\"--\", dashes=(5, 10), color=\"gray\", linewidth=0.5)\n",
    "    ax2.minorticks_on()\n",
    "    ax2.legend()\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Tracé du sous-jacent et des strikes\n",
    "    ax3.plot(time, V[path, :]*100, label=\"Variance\", color='red', marker='+')\n",
    "    ax3.grid(linestyle=\"--\", dashes=(5, 10), color=\"gray\", linewidth=0.5)\n",
    "    ax3.minorticks_on()\n",
    "    ax3.set_xlabel(\"Time\")\n",
    "    ax3.set_ylabel(\"%\")\n",
    "    ax3.legend()\n",
    "\n",
    "    plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "    plt.show()"
   ]
  }
